{"type":"message","id":"e683c343","parentId":"0eac0a81","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:59:16.441Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_duumpl2s46ki_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 224905\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: tic_classifier.py (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune I� empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nGiven the emphasis on the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight and the next action being the TIC experiment, I should focus on implementing that.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- Pulse logs are in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- There's already analysis in `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take now is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me check what pulse logs exist and create a script to analyze them.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending list, I notice the most actionable items are:\r\n1. Define `significance` scoring - this is foundational\r\n2. Implement TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation. I'll create a script that:\r\n1. Analyzes the pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Implements significance scoring\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests that invariant detection IS causal discovery. The next critical step is implementing a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that can identify what persists across pulse gaps versus what decays.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `temporal_invariant_classifier.py` - a script that analyzes pulse logs to detect invariant structures, implement significance scoring, and test the TIC hypothesis against pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\nPhase 1 & 2 unified: compressor finding invariants = discovering causation\r\nSuccess: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass PulseAnalysis:\r\n    path: Path\r\n    invariants: Set[str]  # Content recurring across pulses\r\n    variants: Set[str]   # Content unique to this pulse\r\n    significance_score: float\r\n\r\nclass SignificanceScorer:\r\n    \"\"\"I� encodes both decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_decay: float = 0.7):\r\n        self.lambda_decay = lambda_decay  # Start: I�=0.7\r\n    \r\n    def score(self, content: str, pulse_index: int, total_pulses: int) -> float:\r\n        \"\"\"Score content significance based on persistence and recency\"\"\"\r\n        recency_weight = self.lambda_decay ** (total_pulses - pulse_index)\r\n        persistence_bonus = 1.0 if self._is_persistent(content) else 0.3\r\n        return min(1.0, recency_weight * persistence_bonus)\r\n    \r\n    def _is_persistent(self, content: str) -> bool:\r\n        # Content with structural markers (headers, lists) persists more\r\n        structural_markers = ['##', '###', '-', '*', '1.', '2.', '3.']\r\n        return any(marker in content for marker in structural_markers)\r\n\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n    Finds invariant structure across session gaps (gap = compression)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    INVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n        r'^#+\\s',           # Headers\r\n        r'^\\*\\*.*\\*\\*:',    # Bold labels\r\n        r'^- \\[ \\]',        # Unchecked items\r\n        r'^- \\[x\\]',        # Checked items\r\n        r'^\\d+\\.',          # Numbered lists\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_decay: float = 0.7):\r\n        self.scorer = SignificanceScorer(lambda_decay)\r\n        self.corpus: List[str] = []\r\n    \r\n    def load_pulses(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\") -> List[PulseAnalysis]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load and analyze all pulse logs\"\"\"\r\n        logs_path = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(logs_path.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        \r\n        analyses = []\r\n        for i, pulse_file in enumerate(pulse_files):\r\n            content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n            self.corpus.append(content)\r\n            \r\n            invariants = self._extract_invariants(content)\r\n            variants = self._extract_variants(content, invariants)\r\n            significance = self.scorer.score(content, i, len(pulse_files))\r\n            \r\n            analyses.append(PulseAnalysis(\r\n                path=pulse_file,\r\n                invariants=invariants,\r\n                variants=variants,\r\n                significance_score=significance\r\n            ))\r\n        \r\n        return analyses\r\n    \r\n    def _extract_invariants(self, content: str) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract content patterns that indicate structure (invariants)\"\"\"\r\n        invariants = set()\r\n        \r\n        # Extract headers\r\n        headers = re.findall(r'^(#{1,6}\\s+.+)$', content, re.MULTILINE)\r\n        for h in headers:\r\n            level = len(h) - len(h.lstrip('#'))\r\n            invariants.add(f\"HEADER_L{level}:{h.strip('#').\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 22:49:36"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2187,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 224905\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: tic_classifier.py (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune I� empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nGiven the emphasis on the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight and the next action being the TIC experiment, I should focus on implementing that.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- Pulse logs are in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- There's already analysis in `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take now is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me check what pulse logs exist and create a script to analyze them.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending list, I notice the most actionable items are:\r\n1. Define `significance` scoring - this is foundational\r\n2. Implement TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation. I'll create a script that:\r\n1. Analyzes the pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Implements significance scoring\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for this.\r\